# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization
* text=auto

# Shell scripts are executed INSIDE Linux containers -- the field-device
# sims run `sh -c "set-gateway.sh && <sim>"`, setup.sh drives the stack, etc.
# On a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true these would come out CRLF,
# and a CRLF in a shebang makes the Linux kernel look for `/bin/sh\r`: the
# container then dies with `set-gateway.sh: not found` and crash-loops, which
# breaks `docker compose build` and scripts/smoke-test.ps1 on Windows.
# Pin them to LF so a Windows build produces working images.
*.sh text eol=lf
